  <static seed="94" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionAdditionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>Martha walked <m>{{\frac{1}{7}}}</m> of a mile in the morning, and then walked <m>{{\frac{1}{12}}}</m> of a mile in the afternoon. How far did Martha walk altogether?</p>
<p>Martha walked a total of <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of a mile.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{19}{84}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is an addition problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{7}}} + {{\frac{1}{12}}} 
      \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 12}{7 \cdot 12}+\frac{1 \cdot 7}{12 \cdot 7} \\
      \amp = \frac{12}{84} + \frac{7}{84} \\
      \amp = \frac{12+7}{84} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{19}{84}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Martha walked a total of <m>{{\frac{19}{84}}}</m> miles altogether.</p>
</solution>
